<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>The Premier League fixtures for the 2020-21 season have been revealed, with the opening weekend throwing up a huge game between champions Liverpool and newly-promoted Leeds United.</p>

<p>Manchester United and Manchester City will not feature in the first gameweek, which starts on Saturday September 12, after their European exploits. </p>

<p>Elsewhere, Jose Mourinho's Tottenham host Everton in their first game of the new season, while Arsenal kick-off their campaign away at Fulham.</p>

<p>Chelsea and Wolves will both play on Monday, September 14 away at Brighton and Sheffield United respectively. </p>

